definitions: To produce (a book, newspaper, etc.) by means of a mechanical press involving the transfer of text or images to paper.
To produce a hard copy of (data) from a computer.
To write (text) clearly without joining the letters.
To make a mark or design on (fabric or other material).
To produce a photographic print from (a negative).
examples: The company will print the new brochures next week.
Please print the document for me.
Print your name clearly at the top of the form.
They print patterns on the cloth.
He learned to print his own photos.
